Sentencas: Samarium-doped ceria (SDC) is considered as an alternative electrolyte material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) because its conductivity is higher than that of commonly used yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ).
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Single-Layer SDC and Multilayer SDC/YSZ/SDC Electrolytes

Sentencas: The paper compares the properties of anode-supported SOFCs with magnetron sputtered single-layer SDC and multilayer SDC/YSZ/SDC thin-film electrolyte, with the YSZ blocking layer 0.5, 1, and 1.5 & mu;m thick.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Single-Layer SDC and Multilayer SDC/YSZ/SDC Electrolytes

Sentencas: The thickness of the upper and lower SDC layers of the multilayer electrolyte are constant and amount to 3 and 1 & mu;m, respectively.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Single-Layer SDC and Multilayer SDC/YSZ/SDC Electrolytes

Sentencas: The thickness of single-layer SDC electrolyte is 5.5 & mu;m.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Single-Layer SDC and Multilayer SDC/YSZ/SDC Electrolytes

Sentencas: The SOFC performance is studied by measuring current-voltage characteristics and impedance spectra in the range of 500-800 & DEG;C. X-ray diffraction and scanning electron microscopy are used to investigate the structure of the deposited electrolyte and other fuel cell layers.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Single-Layer SDC and Multilayer SDC/YSZ/SDC Electrolytes

Sentencas: SOFCs with the single-layer SDC electrolyte show the best performance at 650 & DEG;C. At this temperature, open circuit voltage and maximum power density are 0.8 V and 651 mW/cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Single-Layer SDC and Multilayer SDC/YSZ/SDC Electrolytes

Sentencas: The formation of the SDC electrolyte with the YSZ blocking layer improves the open circuit voltage up to 1.1 V and increases the maximum power density at the temperatures over 600 & DEG;C. It is shown that the optimal thickness of the YSZ blocking layer is 1 & mu;m.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Single-Layer SDC and Multilayer SDC/YSZ/SDC Electrolytes

Sentencas: The fuel cell with the multilayer SDC/YSZ/SDC electrolyte, with the layer thicknesses of 3/1/1 & mu;m, has the maximum power density of 2263 and 1132 mW/cm(2) at 800 and 650 & DEG;C, respectively.
Titulo: Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Magnetron Sputtered Single-Layer SDC and Multilayer SDC/YSZ/SDC Electrolytes
